# Architecture And Routing

- Keep three-level routing: `/<category>/`, `/<category>/<document>/`, `/<category>/<document>/<variation>/`.
- Treat documents with `parentId: null` as hubs and documents with `parentId` as variations.
- Build URLs from canonical parts only: `category.slug`, `hub.slug`, `variation.slug`.
- Never hardcode full URLs in components when a helper can build them.
- Category pages list hub documents; variation pages must resolve by parent hub.
- `generateStaticParams` must include all published routes and preserve hierarchy.
- `notFound()` should be used for unresolved category/document/variation combinations.

## Data Integrity Checks

- Each `variation.parentId` must reference an existing hub document.
- Do not create cross-category parent-child relations.
- Keep routing logic centralized in `src/lib` helpers when possible.

## File Scope

- `src/app/[category]/page.tsx`
- `src/app/[category]/[document]/page.tsx`
- `src/app/[category]/[document]/[variation]/page.tsx`
- `src/lib/mock.ts`
- `src/app/sitemap.ts`

## Operational Rules

- Any new published hub document must produce a valid `/[category]/[document]/` route.
- Any new published variation must produce a valid `/[category]/[document]/[variation]/` route.
- Variation pages must include full breadcrumb hierarchy (home -> category -> hub -> variation).
- Block changes that break static params generation for published content.

## Done Criteria

- `npm run build` succeeds.
- No generated route points to missing category/hub/variation references.
